Program: The Why Factor
Title: Monogamy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01f89zy
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 26 Aug 2013
Around the world people have different rules for their relationships - rules often dictated by culture and religion. In many societies the most important of these is sexual fidelity - true love and monogamy are expected to go hand in hand - but why should love mean forsaking all others? And what happens to relationships when monogamy is cast adrift? (Image of couples kissing and celebrating the eve of Valentine's Day. Credit: Getty Images) Show less